social_posts.post_text:
Struggling with hooks and blocks? A drill I saw a few years back from a great instructor @andrewricegolf can help to get rid of the flip through impact. 
•
My biggest mentor @mcleangolf says “Swing Left to swing right.” The separation of club and ball post impact is key. The swing is a circle that works towards the target line in the downswing and inside the target line on the through swing. If your club works too much “down the target line” post impact this can lead to an excessive inside to out path, causing hooks and blocks. 
•
This drill will help neutralize your swing direction and create a more consistent face to path relationship. Swipe to see the videos explaining the drill.
•
•
To setup the drill:
1) Place one alignment stick parallel to target line just outside the toe of your club. 
2) Put ball on tee at or just above ground height.
3) Place second alignment stick angled away from you about 18-24” in front of the ball inside the target line. 
This will create a window for your ball start line and a visual of where the clubhead needs to travel post impact.

social_posts.post_text: 🛑STOP HITTING IT FAT!🛑 If you struggle shifting your pressure into your lead side on the downswing, then the “Step & Swing” drill is great way to feel correct pressure shift. I learned this drill from @mcleangolf during my years in TX. As your backswing gets to lead arm parallel to ground, step with your lead foot and try to put your spikes down in the normal setup position. This will help you to recenter your pressure at the top of the swing and shift pressure forward in the downswing. Moving your low point of the swing forward to help achieve ball first contact.

Great drill to improve radius management in the golf swing. @alexisnicolebelton maintaining width in transition to improve her shot pattern. Y’all better watch out for her on the celebrity circuit soon @mfentertainmentx
•
Setup:
1) Pull-up band under the lead arm
2) Band hooked into trail thumb
3) Firm tightness on band throughout motion until at least impact
4) DON’T DROP THE BAND

Neutralizing swing direction using the now infamous @officialtommyfleetwood drill with @ajq_21 
•
Austin was struggling with the ball over drawing, especially in his longer clubs. Using the drill station he shifted his avg. swing direction from +4.2 back to +.8 which creates a more consistent pattern.

Are you sick and tired of chunking and blading chip shots around the green? I have a few keys to focus on in setup and your motion to improve your shots around the green. Swipe to see the videos where I discuss more in depth. 
•
The 🔑:
1) Ball position forward of middle
2) 60-70% pressure on lead foot
3) Point butt end of grip at first belt loop (just inside lead hip)
4) Return shaft to setup position at impact

Green reading is a SKILL. This means it can be learned. The @tourreadgolf app gives you the tools to improve your SKILL and will help you take it to the golf course!

There are tons of Tour players using this app to train their green reading skills. Take your green reading to the next level and golf becomes way more fun!!

Solid first event of the year on the @kornferrytour for the lefty @jtrentphillips 68-74-70-69=281(-7). This will help him improve his status for the rest of the year. 
•
Here we are working on maintaining a more neutral lead wrist throughout the backswing…his tendency is for his lead wrist to work into too much extension. This causes his club to start down too steep in transition. Neutral position for him at the top allows his club to shallow slightly in transition which allows him to get the golf ball started in his desired window.

social_posts.post_text:
Georgia, meet Taylor 🤝

Hometown: Athens, GA 🐶
Current town: Lake Oconee⛳️

After playing college golf at UGA and NC State, Taylor moved to Texas for nine years. In an effort to stay cool in the Texas heat (and for absolutely no other enjoyable reason) he became a fan of local beers like Shiner and Deep Ellum. 🍺

Thankfully, four years ago Taylor moved back to the Peach State. Today he’s the Lead Golf Instructor at The Kingdom-Reynolds Lake Oconee and named by Golf Digest as one of the Best Young Teachers in America for 2023-2024. He enjoys his days helping others improve their game, loves getting back to Athens to see the dawgs in Sanford on a Saturday, and still drinks local beer like Peach State Lite. To Taylor, there is no better place to enjoy an ice cold PSL than after a round of golf in this summer heat. Cheers to drinking local, coming home, and helping bad golfers become less bad golfers! 🍻🤷‍♂️🏌️

A big thank you to @devan_bonebrake and @golfpass for the feature of the #helldrill that I learned from @scottcowxcertified 
•
We had an impressive lineup of instructors while we were in TX working for @mcleangolf @jwinstruction @justin_poyntergolf @davidangelottiputting @tylerslocumgolf
